1
00:00:11,958 --> 00:00:16,916
♪

2
00:01:34,958 --> 00:01:37,041
[NARRATOR] Kurama is now
in the throes of battle

3
00:01:37,125 --> 00:01:38,875
with Team Toguro's Karasu.

4
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:40,291
With this being
the first match

5
00:01:40,375 --> 00:01:41,791
in the Dark
Tournament's finals,

6
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:44,458
Kurama is determined to win
by whatever means necessary.

7
00:01:44,541 --> 00:01:46,375
The mystical potion he received

8
00:01:46,458 --> 00:01:48,000
has taken effect
just in time,

9
00:01:48,083 --> 00:01:50,500
barely saving him
from Karasu's deadly bomb

10
00:01:50,583 --> 00:01:53,125
and transforming
him into Yoko Kurama.

11
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:54,958
Will this be enough,

12
00:01:55,041 --> 00:01:58,833
or will the legendary demon
have to give up his life?

13
00:02:32,416 --> 00:02:34,875
[crowd gasps]

14
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:02,333
The Ojigi is truly
gifted species of plant.

15
00:03:02,416 --> 00:03:04,875
It can sense the smallest
amount of movement.

16
00:03:04,958 --> 00:03:07,625
Even something as
insignificant as a muscle spasm.

17
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:15,291
So you see, it's useless to run,

18
00:03:15,375 --> 00:03:17,333
it would only make you
easier to catch.

19
00:03:29,291 --> 00:03:31,875
Oh wow, folks! Things are
really starting to heat up.

20
00:03:31,958 --> 00:03:34,916
It's dinner time and
Karasu's the catch of the day!

21
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,791
This is it!!
He's plant food!

22
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,541
Kick his ass, Kurama!!

23
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:41,708
It must be hard for
you to lose control.

24
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:31,208
The Ojigi also
responds to aggression,

25
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:34,000
so it will be all the
more vicious once you attack.

26
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:41,583
You're going
to have to come up

27
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:44,666
with a smart way to
kill it, or else, bang.

28
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:21,333
I thought it was going to
last much longer than that.

29
00:05:21,416 --> 00:05:23,666
I would've liked to have
toyed with him a little

30
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,875
before he died.

31
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:29,083
That was the most beautiful
thing I've ever seen.

32
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:31,000
Kurama's plant
just grabbed Karasu

33
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:32,708
and juiced him
like a fresh orange,

34
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,166
I never would've thought botany

35
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,166
could be so
deliciously gruesome!

36
00:05:36,250 --> 00:05:37,958
Kurama sure showed
that punk what was up!

37
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:40,916
And he closed the deal
in a measly five minutes!

38
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,458
Eat that, Toguro!

39
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:44,916
Yes! Two more
wins and it's done.

40
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,458
Holy Toledo, I didn't
know Kurama could do that.

41
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:53,166
Remind me never
to make that guy mad.

42
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:57,125
Oh Koenma, sir!
Koenma, sir, look up!

43
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:58,250
[KOENMA]
What?!

44
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,125
I'm sorry sir, but
your face is leaking!

45
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,291
[KOENMA] Crap...

46
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,083
This is always so embarrassing.

47
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,916
I can't believe it,
Kurama won.

48
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,833
Don't get me wrong,
I love my bro,

49
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:15,000
but it's nice to see
someone not embarrass himself.

50
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,583
Hey Juri, get the lead out!

51
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:30,583
It's time to
tell us who's won!

52
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,791
Oh, right!!

53
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:37,083
Um, it looks like Karasu's
been soundly defeated

54
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:40,875
and the winner of the first
match is Team Urameshi's Kurama!

55
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:45,916
Hey,
stay back!

56
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:08,708
[KARASU] I wouldn't
count me out just yet.

57
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:13,583
Oh I'm so, so sorry,
that was entirely my fault.

58
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:15,083
Everyone, forget
what I just said!

59
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,791
The fight will
now continue, okay!

60
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:18,125
This is insane!

61
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:24,500
I don't know how much
more of this I can take.

62
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:33,083
You look surprised Yoko.

63
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:35,791
Did you think that was
the last you'd see of me?

64
00:07:35,875 --> 00:07:38,500
Karasu has lost
his dear old mask.

65
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:42,000
Indeed he did.
Take a few steps back Sakyo.

66
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,791
Things are about
to get hazardous.

67
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:57,833
Brace yourself people,
Karasu's back

68
00:07:57,916 --> 00:07:59,791
and he's not too happy!

69
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:02,750
His hair has also changed from
jet black to hyper-glow blonde.

70
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:04,083
To follow the stereotype,

71
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:07,583
that means he's popular
and more aggressive!

72
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:10,916
Can someone fill me in here,
what's going on with his hair?

73
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,833
It's an explicit sign that
he's internalizing his power,

74
00:08:13,916 --> 00:08:15,916
which means the bombs he
creates are now inside of him,

75
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,541
virtually making
him one giant explosive.

76
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:19,833
Are you serious!

77
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,250
Of course I am.

78
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:24,083
If my assumptions are correct,
he's about to detonate.

79
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,291
If you're wise
you'll take cover now.

80
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:48,000
I think you should know
Karasu has no loyalties,

81
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:50,958
he'll kill everyone in this
stadium if he thinks it'll help.

82
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:08,166
[Karasu laughs insanely]

83
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:52,541
Hey, is everyone alright?!

84
00:09:54,166 --> 00:09:55,333
[KOENMA] That idiot
almost killed me.

85
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:57,041
I should have him arrested.

86
00:09:57,791 --> 00:09:59,625
You guys
hear singing?

87
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:05,083
Where's Kurama?!

88
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,333
Now that's devastation!

89
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:14,958
A significant
portion of the ring

90
00:10:15,041 --> 00:10:17,791
has been completely wiped out,
there are corpses everywhere,

91
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,458
and Kurama's
nowhere to be seen!!

92
00:10:20,791 --> 00:10:23,125
[Karasu chuckles]

93
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:36,458
Oh wow! That Kurama
is like a nasty virus!

94
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:37,625
You just can't get rid of him!

95
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:39,083
However, it does look like

96
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:40,791
this last explosion
has taken its toll,

97
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:44,625
because now he's back
in his original human form!

98
00:10:44,708 --> 00:10:46,666
Ah, crap!
The potion wore off.

99
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,625
Now he's really
gonna have to wing it!

100
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,583
I don't get it!

101
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:52,833
He said that stuff's supposed
to last fifteen minutes!

102
00:10:52,916 --> 00:10:54,958
That's it, the next
time I see Suzuki,

103
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:56,750
I'm moppin' the
floor with his face!

104
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:03,875
[KURAMA THINKS]
I don't understand,

105
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:07,416
I was sure that the
potion lasted longer.

106
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,125
For some reason it's
effects are weakening

107
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:12,041
every time I use it!

108
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:19,333
Forgive me for disturbing
your train of thought, but,

109
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:22,208
shouldn't you take
this time to pray?

110
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:26,791
After all, you are
about to meet your creator.

111
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,125
[KARASU] You can ask him
why he flawed with you.

112
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:34,625
[Karasu laughs]

113
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:02,541
You're too weak Kurama,

114
00:12:02,625 --> 00:12:05,666
you can't even control the
most basic of your attacks.

115
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:08,041
Make this easier on
both of us and give in.

116
00:12:08,125 --> 00:12:09,875
I promise it
won't hurt too much.

117
00:12:11,958 --> 00:12:13,291
Kurama!!

118
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:14,750
[KOTO] Wow fight fans,

119
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,541
the suspense is in the air
here at the Dark Tournament,

120
00:12:16,625 --> 00:12:19,416
because everybody knows that
one more solid attack by Karasu

121
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,166
means curtains
for you-know-who!

122
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:24,416
If you think about it, death
really isn't so frightening.

123
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:27,333
Who knows, you might
actually enjoy it.

124
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:58,083
Aw man! Kurama's launching a
full blown assault on Karasu,

125
00:12:58,166 --> 00:12:59,875
but so far it's
completely useless!

126
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:01,541
Blondie's dodging each punch.

127
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:04,583
I can't take it anymore,
I need to see some blood!!!

128
00:13:04,666 --> 00:13:08,666
He has a plan. It's obvious
in the way that he moves.

129
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,916
I think you've
finally lost your mind.

130
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,791
If you come any closer,
you are a dead man.

131
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:22,208
I will not be afraid of
something that I cannot see!

132
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,708
[KARASU] You're just
full of surprises,

133
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:40,125
but I thought
you'd be more original.

134
00:13:43,958 --> 00:13:45,958
You really thought
this would work?

135
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,458
[KARASU]
It's called tact, Kurama,

136
00:13:49,541 --> 00:13:52,291
you should consider using some.

137
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:56,333
That stupid jerk is really
starting to piss me off!

138
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:59,166
He knows what Kurama's
gonna do before he does it!

139
00:14:00,208 --> 00:14:02,625
[KOENMA] Guys, I don't
think he's gonna make it.

140
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:08,125
I must congratulate
you though.

141
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:09,333
You've injured
me more than once

142
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:11,791
and that is
practically unheard of.

143
00:14:21,750 --> 00:14:24,416
Time to say bombs away!!

144
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:27,666
That's what I
call, my mad bomb.

145
00:14:29,041 --> 00:14:30,791
Out of luck,
now your...

146
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:42,000
No Kurama!

147
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:57,250
[Karasu chuckles]

148
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:04,166
Don't move another inch Kurama!
You're surrounded by bombs!

149
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:18,708
Didn't you say you chose
not to be afraid of things

150
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:20,250
you could not see?

151
00:15:20,625 --> 00:15:22,875
Well here's a
better look.

152
00:15:22,958 --> 00:15:24,500
You know that
this entire battle

153
00:15:24,583 --> 00:15:26,541
has been an
exercise in futility.

154
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:30,541
[KARASU]
You're weak,

155
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:32,791
you're tired,

156
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:35,166
you're powerless,

157
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:37,083
you're pathetic.

158
00:15:37,958 --> 00:15:40,333
Yet it seems you
have a masochistic streak

159
00:15:40,416 --> 00:15:42,250
that wants indulging.

160
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:44,875
So, here goes.

161
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:03,666
I can't watch
him suffer like this!

162
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,083
Karasu is such a bastard.

163
00:16:05,166 --> 00:16:06,708
He's clearly playing
with him now.

164
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:08,833
I wish he would
just get this over with.

165
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:11,333
I don't ever want to hear
you talk like that again.

166
00:16:11,416 --> 00:16:12,625
Kurama will beat him!

167
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:15,208
Kurama can't die,
he just can't!

168
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:17,125
I've lost one person
I love to Toguro's Team,

169
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:18,916
I won't lose another!

170
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,416
Is he done yet?

171
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:24,958
Probably not, he deeply
enjoys the suffering of others.

172
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:29,000
Well, I suppose the two of us

173
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:31,625
have more in
common than I thought.

174
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:47,291
Your red hair is perfect for
that fiery spirit that I admire.

175
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:48,750
You know that's
why I've decided

176
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:51,000
to leave your
beautiful face unharmed.

177
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:54,125
I may not be able to keep you,
but I'll always have the memory

178
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:56,583
of your face to give comfort.

179
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:06,166
[[KURAMA THINKS] You couldn't
have been more wrong

180
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:09,208
about my so-called
lack of tact, Karasu.

181
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:11,250
Just as wrong as
believing that mark on your

182
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:14,000
chest is only a
harmless scratch.

183
00:17:14,791 --> 00:17:16,916
[KURAMA THINKS] The smell of
the wound so close to your heart

184
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,416
will be more than enough
for a bloodthirsty plant.

185
00:17:21,083 --> 00:17:22,500
[[KURAMA THINKS]
You may not think I posses

186
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,375
the ability to summon a plant.

187
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:27,125
But you will soon find out that
you are wrong there as well.

188
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:30,250
I can summon once more,
in exchange for my life!

189
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:36,791
Alright, let's end this.

190
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:04,125
No!!!

191
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:20,000
Yes!! Let 'em
have it, Karasu!!

192
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:23,375
Do it already!
Finish him, finish him!

193
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:33,708
The crowd is going
wild here and rightly so!

194
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:35,916
Kurama's down and I don't
think he's getting back up!

195
00:18:37,041 --> 00:18:39,625
Just do it.
We don't have all day!

196
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:40,958
Gimme that you big oaf!

197
00:18:42,458 --> 00:18:43,583
Juri, count!!

198
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:46,416
Please for the love
of good hygiene, count!!

199
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,125
Okay!!!

200
00:18:48,208 --> 00:18:49,541
He has until
the count of ten!

201
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:52,291
If he stays down,
Karasu wins.

202
00:18:52,375 --> 00:18:53,708
One!

203
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:58,666
[JURI]
Two, Three, Four,

204
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:03,416
Five, Six, Seven!

205
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,458
[KURAMA THINKS] I cannot
hesitate. I barely have

206
00:19:09,541 --> 00:19:14,000
enough Life Energy left.
I must destroy him now!

207
00:19:14,083 --> 00:19:19,166
You should have stayed down, but
I guess that's not your style.

208
00:19:20,291 --> 00:19:21,125
Now.

209
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:24,833
[KURAMA THINKS]
I may die, but at least

210
00:19:24,916 --> 00:19:26,875
it will end in a draw!!!

211
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:58,166
It can't be...

212
00:19:58,250 --> 00:20:01,166
Where did he find
the strength to do this?

213
00:20:15,666 --> 00:20:19,583
[crowd gasps]

214
00:20:19,666 --> 00:20:20,666
His life!

215
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,250
It's fading!!

216
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:27,666
Oh Kurama
please get up!

217
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:30,083
He isn't moving,
do you think he's dead?

218
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:32,250
Of course he's not!
He can't be!

219
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:36,541
Accept it Botan. He sacrificed
himself to kill Karasu.

220
00:20:36,625 --> 00:20:37,750
Please wake up!!

221
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:51,666
[KURAMA THINKS] I'm alive.

222
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:03,708
[KURAMA THINKS] I don't
understand, how did I make it?

223
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:07,458
I gave all of
my Life Energy.

224
00:21:07,541 --> 00:21:08,916
Of course!

225
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:13,250
Each time I take the potion,

226
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:15,958
the duration of
its effects shorten.

227
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:19,375
They shorten because every time
I transform into Yoko Kurama,

228
00:21:19,458 --> 00:21:22,125
I retain some of his power.

229
00:21:22,208 --> 00:21:24,291
That's how I survived.

230
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,958
And that's how
we win this, yeah!

231
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:32,041
He's a little jacked up,
but I'd say he won!

232
00:21:32,125 --> 00:21:33,750
Um, hold on.

233
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:37,541
[NARRATOR] Kurama's willingness
to sacrifice himself for his

234
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:39,791
team has allowed him to
escape with his life.

235
00:21:39,875 --> 00:21:42,041
After the first
fight of the final round,

236
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:45,541
Kurama is standing and
Karasu is laid to waste.

237
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:49,500
But what important message
is Juri waiting to tell?

238
00:21:52,541 --> 00:21:54,000
[KUWABARA] Kuwabara's
got the mike!

239
00:21:54,083 --> 00:21:56,500
And match two of the
finals is about to start,

240
00:21:56,583 --> 00:21:59,125
once Juri says her
thing and shocks us all.

241
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:02,708
Hiei's gonna face off against
the freaky quiet man Bui.

242
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:05,916
I think it's a bad idea
since he's like half the size

243
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,958
of that axe, but when's
tiny-boy ever listened to me??

244
00:22:09,041 --> 00:22:11,500
It's gonna be brute
strength mixed with surprises.

245
00:22:11,583 --> 00:22:14,000
We'll hear Bui's voice
